7. No religious influence on divorce

Belgium is a country without a State religion, which means that no institutions hold power over divorce matters. That openness and liberty allow couples of different faiths or none to make their own decisions, and for those faiths that do have divorce requirements to have them agreed on by the Courts.

8. The fastest divorce for children in the world

A woman in Belgium recently filed for divorce and was granted one in a duration of just 5 days. Although judges have the power to drastically reduce the waiting period for the divorce of children, the fastest-ever divorce is one of ten days, granted back in 1971.

9. PreNups are not yet recognized by the Family Court

Although a marriage contract is a common part of most weddings, there is no power for prenuptial agreements to be enforced by the family judge. Social values keep family law in line with the majority of the willing participant, even when it comes to setting the conditions for what is expected to happen in the event of a divorce.
